course: main course
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

In #oven-ready tray{}, combine @cream sauce base{4%oz}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, 
and @water{1/2%cup}; season with @pepper{}. Stir in @tortelloni{9%oz}, @peas{4%oz}, 
and @garlic powder{1%tsp} until thoroughly coated.

> For 4 servings, divide ingredients between two trays, using 1/2 cup water for each tray.

Drizzle @pesto{4%tbsp} evenly over tortelloni mixture.

Cover tray tightly with #foil{}; place on top of a #baking sheet{}. Bake on top rack 
(be sure your oven has preheated!) until tortelloni is tender and sauce is bubbly, 
~{25-30%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, bake two trays side by side on top rack.

Once tortelloni is done, carefully remove foil (watch out for steam!). Sprinkle 
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} over the top, then evenly drizzle with @olive oil{}. 
Return to oven and bake, uncovered, until panko is golden brown, ~{5-7%minutes} more.

Divide tortelloni bake between shallow #bowls{} and serve.